      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, I need help writing a rejection email for a candidate. They made it all the way to the final round for our Senior DevOps role here in Austin, so it's a tough one. They had really strong technical skills and a great culture fit, but we just went with someone who had a bit more experience with Kubernetes orchestration. Can you draft something that is professional and kind but firm, so they don't feel like they wasted their time?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Subject: Your Application: Senior DevOps Role at [Company Name]\n\nDear [Candidate's Name],\n\nThank you for your interest in the Senior DevOps position at [Company Name] and for the effort you put into the interview process. We truly appreciate the time and energy you invested in meeting with our team. After careful consideration, we have decided to move forward with another candidate who possesses a slightly more extensive experience with Kubernetes orchestration.\n\nWhile your skills and enthusiasm are commendable, we believe that this particular role requires a specific set of expertise that we felt the other candidate better met. We were impressed with your technical abilities and your fit with our company culture, and we hope you will consider applying for future opportunities that align more closely with your strengths.\n\nThank you once again for your interest in [Company Name], and we wish you the best in your job search and future career endeavors.\n\nSincerely,\n\n[Your Name]\n[Your Position]\n[Company Name]",
